  "texts": [
    "Considering that the handled data mostly comes from patients, ethical and privacy concerns are highly significant.",
    "Since most of the scenarios may occur in relatively stable environments like smart homes or healthcare centers, sensitivity to the environment can be kept low.",
    "Though the possibility of deliberate enactment in a healthcare setup is relatively lower, it is still set to moderate to address the exaggeration of symptoms by some patients.",
    "As patients and individuals seeking health solutions are the primary targets in this use case, user discomfort can be compromised; hence, it can be kept at a low priority.",
    "The data availability is set to moderate primarily because while health monitoring systems can generate a substantial volume of data, access to this data may be constrained by privacy regulations and the personal preferences of the patients involved.Figure 12 shows the scores assigned to each modality combination according to the specific requirements of the healthcare and well-being scenario."
